HIGHLIGHTS OF THE NEW RELEASES
 
 Adelsheim Pinot Noir 2000, Elizabeth's Reserve Pinot Noir 99, 
Goldschmidt Vineyard Pinot Noir 99,Bryan Creek Pinot Noir 99
http://www.oregongourmet.com/adelsheimvineyard.html 
  
 Domaine Drouhin Pinot Noir 99 $39.99
A beautiful wine, elegant and polished. The nose is delicate, with hints of truffle, black pepper, warm black fruit, cassis, and a hint of earthiness. The flavors are of black plum, cassis, hints of saddle leather, vanilla, subtle layers and layer of anise, licorice, pepper, allspice, cinnamon, red cherry, fresh woodsy forest. The length and depth of the finish distinguishes this wine. Cellar up to ten years, but it's beautiful now.http://www.oregongourmet.com/domainedrouhinpinotnoir99.html 
L'Ecole #41 Pepper Bridge Apogee 99 $45.99
L'Ecole #41 Merlot Walla Walla Seven Hills 99 
(Wine Spec rating 92 points for 98 vintage) $42.99
We are so pleased to announce that we now carry the full line of L'Ecole's wines in stock, after
years of spotty availability. The Syrah is sold out, but everything else is available at great prices!
Wine reviews and ordering here:
http://www.oregongourmet.com/lecole41winery.html 
Argyle Pinot Noir 2000 $17.59 SALE! Regular $19.99
Argyle's 2000 vintage Pinot Noir is available now and it's time to stock up on this excellent value before
the reviews come out. The 2000 Pinot Noir is a bright, deep ruby red. The aromas are of a complex combination of spices (cardamom, cinnamon, vanilla), black fruits, and earth. Flavors lean toward black fruits; black cherries and blackberries with a small earthy and seasoned cedar component.. Medium-bodied, this wine is unctuous with big fruit and a firm tannin finish sanded by sweetness from the fruit flavors.. The finish is long with a nice balance between sweet, ripe fruit and soft, chewy tannins. Drink now or cellar three to four years.
http://www.oregongourmet.com/argylewines.html 
  
 Penner Ash Pinot Noir 2000 $49.99; Penner Ash Syrah 2000 $35.99
Lynn Penner-Ash has left Rex Hill to spend fulltime at her family winery, and here is their new Pinot Noir and their very limited Syrah (100 cases made). The Pinot is a blend of grapes from Rex Hill's Jacob-Hart, Seven Springs, and Weber vineyards. Order now for delivery in Summer 2002.
 http://www.avalonwine.com/Penner-Ash-Wine-Cellars.htm 
 Reininger Walla Walla Valley Winery
http://www.avalonwine.com/reininger.htm 
 Merlot 99 $29.99 - A very fruit forward, well-balanced wine displaying tantalizing flavors. The nose greets you with black fruits, hints of tobacco, and whispers of coconut and vanillin. The mouth bursts with bing cherries, while the finish suggests essences of Russian olive and light oak. Elegant structure gives this wine moderate aging ability though is very enjoyable now.
Cabernet Sauvignon 99 $32.99- A very rich and complex wine, dark red in color. Flavors of ripe plum and vanillin lead off the nose with hints of spice, mocha and black fruits in the mouth. The well-rounded tannins make the expansive mouth feel soft yet structured. A big, lingering finish completes this gorgeous wine. 92 Points Wine Enthusiast
 Syrah 99  $29.99- A wine possessing deep, rich color. The nose reflects aromas of baking spices and blueberries while the mouth hints of raspberries and apricots. The very light influence of oak allows the true essence of the fruit be revealed. The wine is very soft in the mouth with well-integrated tannins that define a very balanced wine with an elegant, seamless finish. Double Gold, San Francisco International Wine Competition 2001http://www.avalonwine.com/reininger.htm 
Seven Hills Winery
http://www.avalonwine.com/seven-hills-winery.htm 
There's a new article by our staff writer Christina Kelly 
on the Seven Hills Winery here:http://www.avalonwine.com/seven-hills-winery.htm 
Syrah 99- very limited Softer tannins and very broad, full mid-palate flavors characterize this wine. The aroma is of red fruits and smoky Syrah varietal character, surrounded by complex oak tones of spice and vanilla. There's a great balance on the palate, with a natural harmony and brightness between fruit, acidity and tannins.
Order here:http://www.oregongourmet.com/sevenhillswinery.html 
 
